    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="377"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Seward presents his compliments to Lord Lyons, and has the honor to transmit
                    herewith to his lordship a copy of a letter of yesterday from the Secretary of
                    War, upon the subject of the condition of the prisoners confined at Fort
                    Delaware, respecting which Mr. Seward had the honor to converse with Lord Lyons
                    a few days since.</p>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-missing-head-in-printed-volume">[Untitled]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington City</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-28">
                                <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28, 1863.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                        of your letter of the 27th instant, and to inform you, in reply, that orders
                        have been issued for an immediate and thorough inspection into the condition
                        of the prisoners confined at Fort Delaware.</p>
                    <p>Very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>EDWIN M. STANTON, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of War</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Secretary of State.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
